10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to soldiers and sailors; allowing
Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs to hire
12 seasonal employees; exempting such employees from
benefits; providing for codification; and providing
13 an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 430 of Title 72, unless there is
19 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. For the purposes of this section, seasonal employees shall
21 be unclassified employees employed by the Oklahoma Department of
22 Veterans Affairs who work less than one thousand six hundred ninety-
23 nine (1,699) hours in any twelve-month period.
24
HB3043 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. The Department may employ seasonal employees throughout the
2 calendar year. Project labor or pro re nata jobs employed by the
3 Department for a period of time necessary to complete a project or
4 fulfill the need shall be in the unclassified service of the state,
5 as provided by the Oklahoma Personnel Act, Section 840-1.1 et seq.
6 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes. Such employees shall not be
7 entitled to paid leave, paid holidays, retirement, health, dental or
8 life insurance, and shall be exempt from any laws, rules, or
9 practices providing for such benefits.
10 C. The Department, in its annual budget request, shall include
11 a summary of the use of project labor, which shall include the
12 number of workers employed under the provisions of this section and
13 the total wages paid to these employees.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
15
16 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
OVERSIGHT, dated 02/16/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended.
